---
import LandingLayout from '@/layouts/LandingLayout.astro';
---

<LandingLayout
  title="VMFlux | Professional Navisworks export workflows"
  description="Professional Navisworks export workflows for OBJ/MTL today, with GLB/glTF and properties export coming next."
  includeOrgSchema={true}
>
  <section class="border-b border-border bg-background">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-14 lg:px-8 lg:py-16">
      <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr_0.9fr] lg:items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">
            VMFlux for Navisworks
          </p>

          <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-5xl text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
            Professional export workflows from Navisworks to OBJ/MTL today —
            GLB/glTF and properties next.
          </h1>

          <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-foreground-muted">
            VMFlux helps coordination, visualization, and downstream teams move model data
            out of Navisworks with cleaner structure, material-aware output, and a more
            dependable export workflow.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
            <a
              href="/products"
            class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-[#f15a24] px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm transition hover:bg-[#d94d1c]"
            >
              Explore products
            </a>

            <a
              href="/docs"
              class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-border px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-foreground transition hover:bg-muted"
            >
              Read docs
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 border-t border-border pt-8 sm:grid-cols-3">
            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">2024–2026</p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
                Supported Navisworks versions for the current exporter.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">OBJ + MTL</p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
                Available now for practical geometry and material export workflows.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">GLB / glTF</p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
                Coming next alongside properties export for broader downstream use.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid gap-6">
          <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">
              Current product
            </p>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
              VMFlux OBJ Exporter
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
              Focused on dependable OBJ + MTL output from Navisworks with instance-aware
              structure, material naming, and transparency handling aligned to real project use.
            </p>

            <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-sm text-foreground-muted">
              <li>Supports Navisworks 2024 / 2025 / 2026</li>
              <li>Exports OBJ + MTL</li>
              <li>Handles material-aware output</li>
              <li>Designed for production-minded workflows</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="mt-8">
              <a
                href="/products"
                class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-border px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-foreground transition hover:bg-muted"
              >
                View product details
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-muted/50 p-8">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">
              Roadmap
            </p>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
              Expanding export coverage
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
              VMFlux is moving toward GLB/glTF and properties export to support richer BIM,
              asset, web-viewer, and automation workflows.
            </p>

            <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-background p-5">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground">GLB / glTF</p>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
                  For modern viewer and real-time pipelines.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-background p-5">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground">Properties export</p>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
                  For structured downstream model data use.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-b border-border bg-muted/50">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-5 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid gap-4 text-sm font-semibold text-foreground md:grid-cols-4">
        <div>Built for coordination workflows</div>
        <div>Material-aware export output</div>
        <div>Downloads via Autodesk App Store</div>
        <div>Support available by email</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-b border-border bg-background">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-16 lg:px-8 lg:py-20">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">
          Why VMFlux
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground sm:text-4xl">
          Built for practical model export, not just demo scenarios.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-5 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
          The focus is reliability, clarity, and useful output structure for teams that
          actually need to move model data into the next step of work.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Reliable geometry export</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
            Export model geometry into structured OBJ output suitable for review,
            visualization, conversion, and downstream reuse.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Material-aware output</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
            Preserve material assignments with MTL output, including real Navisworks
            material naming and transparency handling.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Roadmap for richer exports</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
            Expand toward GLB/glTF and properties export for broader interoperability
            across modern model workflows.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <section class="bg-background">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-16 lg:px-8 lg:py-20">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8 shadow-sm lg:p-9">
        <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_auto] lg:items-center">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">
              Get started
            </p>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
              Explore the current exporter and product direction.
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
              Start with the current OBJ exporter, review documentation, and follow the
              roadmap as VMFlux expands into richer export workflows.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
            <a
              href="/products"
            class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-[#f15a24] px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm transition hover:bg-[#d94d1c]"
            >
              View products
            </a>

            <a
              href="/resources"
              class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-border px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-foreground transition hover:bg-muted"
            >
              Browse resources
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</LandingLayout>